{"info": {"author": "NAGY, Attila", "author_email": "nagy.attila@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python"], "description": "s1crets\n=======\n\ns1crets is a thin Python wrapper to read secrets from cloud resources.\nWherever supported, it can be used to read/update non-encrypted values as well.\n\nInstalling\n----------\n\nInstall and update using `pip`_:\n\n.. code-block:: text\n\n    pip install -U s1crets\n\nA Simple Example\n----------------\n\n.. code-block:: python\n\n    # Using AWS Parameter Store\n    import s1crets.providers.aws\n    ps = s1crets.providers.aws.ParameterStore()\n    ps.get('/prod/databases/mysql/bigdb/root')\n    ps.get_by_path('/prod/databases/mysql')\n    ps.path_exists('/prod/databases/mysql')\n    ps.update('/prod/databases/mysql/bigdb/root', 'S3cr3Tp4Ssw0Rd!^')\n\n    # AWS Secrets Manager\n    sm = s1crets.providers.aws.SecretsManager()\n    sm.get('prod/databases/mysql/bigdb/root')\n    sm.path_exists('prod/databases/mysql')\n    sm.update('prod/databases/mysql/bigdb/root', 'S3cr3Tp4Ssw0Rd!^')\n\n\n.. code-block:: text\n\n    $ s1crets get secrets/json_test\n    {'level1': {'level2': 3}}\n    $ s1crets get secrets/json_test level1\n    {'level2': 3}\n    $ s1crets get secrets/json_test level1 level2\n    3\n\n\n.. _pip: https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/quickstart/", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/bra-fsn/s1crets", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "s1crets", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/s1crets/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/s1crets/", "project_urls": {"Documentation": "https://s1crets.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html", "Homepage": "https://github.com/bra-fsn/s1crets", "Issue tracker": "https://github.com/bra-fsn/s1crets/issues"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/s1crets/0.0.3/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Convenience wrapper for AWS Parameter Store/Secrets Manager", "version": "0.0.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p>s1crets is a thin Python wrapper to read secrets from cloud resources.\nWherever supported, it can be used to read/update non-encrypted values as well.</p>\n<div id=\"installing\">\n<h2>Installing</h2>\n<p>Install and update using <a href=\"https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/quickstart/\" rel=\"nofollow\">pip</a>:</p>\n<pre>pip install -U s1crets\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div id=\"a-simple-example\">\n<h2>A Simple Example</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"c1\"># Using AWS Parameter Store</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">s1crets.providers.aws</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ps</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">s1crets</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">providers</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">aws</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ParameterStore</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ps</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'/prod/databases/mysql/bigdb/root'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ps</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_by_path</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'/prod/databases/mysql'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ps</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">path_exists</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'/prod/databases/mysql'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ps</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">update</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'/prod/databases/mysql/bigdb/root'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'S3cr3Tp4Ssw0Rd!^'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># AWS Secrets Manager</span>\n<span class=\"n\">sm</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">s1crets</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">providers</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">aws</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">SecretsManager</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"n\">sm</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'prod/databases/mysql/bigdb/root'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">sm</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">path_exists</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'prod/databases/mysql'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">sm</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">update</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'prod/databases/mysql/bigdb/root'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'S3cr3Tp4Ssw0Rd!^'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<pre>$ s1crets get secrets/json_test\n{'level1': {'level2': 3}}\n$ s1crets get secrets/json_test level1\n{'level2': 3}\n$ s1crets get secrets/json_test level1 level2\n3\n</pre>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6739535, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "1ae89856580b3cc21e9a7b373160d2bc", "sha256": "f10b186c63619400c9c7740c8f341f14b8f16e0b1dc29b9c7123195f1d7a0eb3"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "s1crets-0.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "1ae89856580b3cc21e9a7b373160d2bc", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 6504, "upload_time": "2020-02-28T14:15:52", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-28T14:15:52.379691Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/9f/51/439916678d6ba901292acdc1bdd0232513e89ae2896099eef7cb38632a65/s1crets-0.0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "288fba51142b39efb4db42b164730d69", "sh